## 2. Diagrama de Secuencia: Flujo de Setup

Detalla la orquestación para crear un nuevo ambiente de pruebas.

```plantuml
@startuml
actor Usuario
participant "CLI / TUI" as UI
participant SetupInteractor as Interactor
participant TestPlanRepository as PlanRepo
participant TestExecutionRepository as ExecRepo
participant TestSetRepository as SetRepo
participant TestRepository as TestRepo

Usuario -> UI : pyjx2 setup --test-plan PROJ-100
UI -> Interactor : execute(config)
activate Interactor

Interactor -> PlanRepo : get_tests(plan_key)
PlanRepo --> Interactor : lista de tests maestros

Interactor -> ExecRepo : resolve(exec_config)
ExecRepo --> Interactor : test_execution_ticket

Interactor -> SetRepo : resolve(set_config)
SetRepo --> Interactor : test_set_ticket

loop por cada test key
    alt mode == clone
        Interactor -> TestRepo : clone(test_key)
        TestRepo --> Interactor : cloned_test_ticket
    else mode == add
        Interactor --> Interactor : usar test_key original
    end
end

Interactor -> SetRepo : add_tests(set_key, list_keys)
Interactor -> ExecRepo : add_test_set(exec_key, set_key)

Interactor --> UI : SetupResult (Keys generadas)
deactivate Interactor
UI --> Usuario : Mostrar Reporte Rich/Logs
@enduml
```

